{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-07",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_07_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "07 - A Mad Tea-party",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.757,
  "page_num": 4,
  "page_total": 4,
  "page_start_sec": 733.6,
  "page_end_sec": 831.32,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 733.6,
      "end": 735.04,
      "text": "----that begins with an M,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 735.14,
      "end": 740.08,
      "text": "such as mouse-traps, and the moon, and memory, and muchness--"
    },
    {
      "start": 740.66,
      "end": 743.18,
      "text": "you know you say things are 'much of a muchness'--"
    },
    {
      "start": 743.78,
      "end": 746.68,
      "text": "did you ever see such a thing as a drawing of a muchness?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 747.11,
      "end": 747.76,
      "text": "\"Really,"
    },
    {
      "start": 747.88,
      "end": 748.7,
      "text": "now you ask me,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 748.88,
      "end": 749.52,
      "text": "said Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 749.64,
      "end": 750.62,
      "text": "very much confused,"
    },
    {
      "start": 751.36,
      "end": 752.28,
      "text": "\"I don't think----\""
    },
    {
      "start": 752.7,
      "end": 753.6,
      "text": "\"Then you shouldn't talk,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 753.8,
      "end": 754.58,
      "text": "said the Hatter."
    },
    {
      "start": 755.66,
      "end": 758.18,
      "text": "This piece of rudeness was more than Alice could bear:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 758.82,
      "end": 760.98,
      "text": "she got up in great disgust and walked off;"
    },
    {
      "start": 761.42,
      "end": 762.96,
      "text": "the Dormouse fell asleep instantly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 763.18,
      "end": 766.5,
      "text": "and neither of the others took the least notice of her going,"
    },
    {
      "start": 766.96,
      "end": 768.46,
      "text": "though she looked back once or twice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 768.68,
      "end": 770.78,
      "text": "half hoping that they would call after her:"
    },
    {
      "start": 771.54,
      "end": 772.7,
      "text": "the last time she saw them,"
    },
    {
      "start": 772.84,
      "end": 775.3,
      "text": "they were trying to put the Dormouse into the teapot."
    },
    {
      "start": 776.03,
      "end": 777.18,
      "text": "\"At any rate"
    },
    {
      "start": 777.2,
      "end": 778.38,
      "text": "I'll never go _there_ again!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 778.62,
      "end": 780.86,
      "text": "said Alice as she picked her way through the wood."
    },
    {
      "start": 781.344,
      "end": 784.62,
      "text": "\"It's the stupidest tea-party I ever was at in all my life!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 785.68,
      "end": 786.82,
      "text": "Just as she said this,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 786.88,
      "end": 789.94,
      "text": "she noticed that one of the trees had a door leading right into it."
    },
    {
      "start": 790.624,
      "end": 791.36,
      "text": "\"That's very curious!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 791.44,
      "end": 791.84,
      "text": "she thought."
    },
    {
      "start": 792.28,
      "end": 793.56,
      "text": "\"But everything's curious to-day."
    },
    {
      "start": 794.24,
      "end": 796.1,
      "text": "I think I may as well go in at once.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 796.22,
      "end": 797.32,
      "text": "And in she went."
    },
    {
      "start": 798.304,
      "end": 800.54,
      "text": "Once more she found herself in the long hall,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 800.72,
      "end": 802.66,
      "text": "and close to the little glass table."
    },
    {
      "start": 803.72,
      "end": 805.34,
      "text": "\"Now I'll manage better this time,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 805.5,
      "end": 806.24,
      "text": "she said to herself,"
    },
    {
      "start": 806.5,
      "end": 808.4,
      "text": "and began by taking the little golden"
    },
    {
      "start": 808.46,
      "end": 811.18,
      "text": "key, and unlocking the door that led into the garden."
    },
    {
      "start": 811.6,
      "end": 813.76,
      "text": "Then she set to work nibbling at the"
    },
    {
      "start": 813.84,
      "end": 814.1,
      "text": "mushroom"
    },
    {
      "start": 814.26,
      "end": 815.7,
      "text": "(she had kept a piece of it in her"
    },
    {
      "start": 815.7,
      "end": 818.0,
      "text": "pocket) till she was about a foot high:"
    },
    {
      "start": 818.64,
      "end": 819.2,
      "text": "then she walked"
    },
    {
      "start": 819.3,
      "end": 820.28,
      "text": "down the little passage:"
    },
    {
      "start": 820.46,
      "end": 824.52,
      "text": "and _then_--she found herself at last in the beautiful garden, among"
    },
    {
      "start": 824.64,
      "end": 827.16,
      "text": "the bright flower-beds and the cool fountains."
    },
    {
      "start": 830.3,
      "end": 831.32,
      "text": "End of chapter 7",
      "para_break": true
    }
  ]
}
